03/08/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- The United States has donated 36 special chemical and radiation warfare suits to Greek police to help boost security during the 2004 Summer Olympics.
US Ambassador Thomas Miller handed over the uniforms to Greek Police Chief Fotis Nasiakos at a special ceremony on Friday (1 August).
A team of US-trained Greek police, firefighters, coastguard personnel and soldiers will use the equipment.
(AFP - 01/08/03)
